"553","<TYPE>EX-99.77E LEGAL"
"554","<SEQUENCE>3"
"555","<FILENAME>legal.txt"
"556","<DESCRIPTION>LEGAL LETTER"
"557","<TEXT>"
"558","On November 4, 2009, the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) and Value"
"559","Line, Inc. (VLI), Value Line Securities, Inc. (currently, EULAV Securities,"
"560","Inc. (ESI or the Distributor)), Jean B. Buttner, former Chairman,"
"561","President and Chief Executive Officer of VLI and David Henigson,"
"562","a former Director and Officer of VLI, settled a matter related"
"563","to brokerage commissions charged by ESI to certain"
"564","Value Line mutual funds (Funds), including the Fund"
"565","from 1986 through November of 2004. The"
"566","matter also involved alleged misleading disclosures provided by VLI to the"
"567","Boards of Directors/Trustees and shareholders of the Funds regarding such"
"568","brokerage commissions. VLI agreed to pay disgorgement in the amount of"
"569","$24,168,979 (representing disgorgement of commissions received), prejudgment"
"570","interest of $9,536,786, and a civil penalty in the amount of $10,000,000."
"571","Also as part of the settlement, Mrs. Buttner and Mr. Henigson each agreed"
"572","to pay a civil penalty, are barred from association with any broker, dealer"
"573","or investment adviser, and are prohibited from serving as an employee,"
"574","officer, director, member of an advisory board, investment adviser or depositor"
"575"," of, or principal underwriter for, a registered investment company or"
"576","affiliated person of such investment adviser, depositor, or principal"
"577","underwriter, subject to a limited exception (limited in scope and for a"
"578","one-year period) for Mrs. Buttner. Pursuant to Section 308(a) of the"
"579","Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002, a fund will be created for VLIs disgorgement,"
"580","interest and penalty (Fair Fund). VLI will bear all costs associated with any"
"581","Fair Fund distribution, including retaining a third-party consultant approved"
"582","by the SEC staff to administer any Fair Fund distribution.  VLI informed the"
"583","Funds Board that it has paid the settlement, continues to have adequate"
"584","liquid assets, and that the resolution of this matter will not have a"
"585","materially adverse effect on the ability of EULAV Asset Management LLC"
"586","(EULAV or the Adviser), the Funds investment adviser, or ESI, the"
"587","Funds distributor, to perform their respective contracts with the Funds."
"588","</TEXT>"
"589","</DOCUMENT>"
"590","</SEC-DOCUMENT>"
"591","-----END PRIVACY-ENHANCED MESSAGE-----"
